they expected the pill to be approved under certain restrictions designed to
ensure women take it safely. If so, it would be a long-awaited victory for
abortion-rights groups. Anti-abortion organizations have battled to keep RU-486
out of the United States since the drug debuted in France in 1988 -- and they
pledged Wednesday to continue fighting the drug if it is sold here.
</P>
