<HEADLINE> Colts Sign RB From Practice Squad  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Running back Lennox Gordon was signed by the
Indianapolis Colts off their practice squad on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Gordon signed as a free agent with the Buffalo Bills last year
and played in eight games, accumulating 38 yards on 11 carries. He
also had one kickoff return for 11 yards.
</P>
<P>
   The Colts also announced the signing of linebacker Phil Glover
to the practice squad.
</P>
<P>
   A seventh-round draft pick of Tennessee last year, Glover was
waived by the Titans on Aug. 26. The 5-foot-11, 241-pound Glover
played in one game on special teams and was inactive for the team's
other 15 games, plus four playoff games.
</P>
<P>
   The Colts also lost free safety Craig Miller from their practice
squad when he signed with the Jacksonville Jaguars.
</P>
</TEXT>
