<HEADLINE> Veteran NFL coach to lead New York/New Jersey XFL team  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) - The New York/New Jersey Hitmen
named longtime NFL assistant Rusty Tillman as their first head
coach Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The Hitmen are the local entry in the XFL, which begins its
inaugural season in February. The team will play its home games at
Giants Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Tillman most recently served as defensive coordinator for the
Indianapolis Colts in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   A linebacker for eight years with the Washington Redskins,
Tillman has been a coach with the Oakland Raiders, Tampa Bay
Buccaneers and Seattle Seahawks.
</P>
<P>
   ''I couldn't be more excited about the opportunity for me to be
one of only eight head coaches in the XFL,'' Tillman said. ''I'm
truly looking forward to coaching in...New Jersey as I have had
many personal relationships and fond memories from coaching and
playing in the area for so many years. I'm also elated that I will
have a chance to interact with Drew Pearson on a regular basis.''
</P>
<P>
   Pearson, the former Dallas Cowboys receiver, is the general
manager of the Hitmen.
</P>
<P>
   ''Rusty brings a wealth of coaching experience to the XFL and
the Hitmen, but it was his accomplishments as a special teams coach
that enabled him to stand above the crowd,'' Pearson said. He has
the ability excel in the New York-New Jersey market because of his
intensity and his aggressive approach to the game.''
</P>
</TEXT>
