<HEADLINE> Second Bomb Explodes in Gaza  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JERUSALEM (AP) -- A roadside bomb exploded near an Israeli
military vehicle in the Gaza Strip on Thursday, the Israeli army
said. No one was injured.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, one Israeli soldier was killed and another was
wounded in a similar attack near the settlement of Netzarim, south
of Gaza City.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday's bombing took place on a security road next to the
fence between Gaza and Israel, between the Erez and Karni crossing
points. The military said the fence was damaged.
</P>
<P>
   Israel television reported that the military believes both
bombings were carried out by the same attackers -- members of one of
the Palestinian security services.
</P>
<P>
   The soldier killed in Wednesday's bombing, Sgt. David Biri, a
19-year-old medic, was buried Thursday in the Jerusalem military
cemetery.
</P>
<P>
   Prime Minister Ehud Barak has demanded that Yasser Arafat's
Palestinian Authority take more effective measures to control
extremists who target Israelis.
</P>
</TEXT>
