<HEADLINE> Driver pleads guilty in hit-and-run accident that killed lawyer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) - A hit-and-run driver who said he was high
on heroin when he fatally struck an attorney in August has pleaded
guilty to felony charges.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis Hopkins, 46, of Buffalo told Erie County Judge Michael
D'Amico Wednesday that he knew he hit something Aug. 15, but was
under the influence of drugs at the time. He said he ''should have
known'' it was a person.
</P>
<P>
   Nino Sciolino, 79, died of head injuries after being struck
while getting out of his parked car about 10:30 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   Hopkins was arrested the next day after eyewitnesses reported
part of the license plate number of Hopkins' fleeing car.
</P>
<P>
   During what was to be a routine pretrial court session, Hopkins
pleaded guilty to single counts of felony leaving the scene of a
fatal accident and drug and hypodermic needle possession charges.
</P>
<P>
   Court officials said Hopkins' criminal record contains at least
29 earlier misdemeanor and felony arrests since the early 1970s in
his native Orleans County.
</P>
</TEXT>
