<HEADLINE> Whitman heads West to raise funds for Franks, local GOP candidates  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - Gov. Christie Whitman heads West on Friday
seeking to strike some California gold for Republican U.S. Senate
candidate Bob Franks and to help four western Republicans raise
funds for their races.
</P>
<P>
   The governor is scheduled to be in Utah on Friday and Saturday
to attend fund-raising events for incumbent Gov. Mike Leavitt, who
is heavily favored to win re-election.
</P>
<P>
   On Monday, Whitman is scheduled to divide her day at California
fund-raisers for Franks and two other GOP candidates seeking
congressional seats there. On Tuesday she will be in Nevada to help
U.S. Senate candidate John Ensign.
</P>
<P>
   Franks is badly overmatched in the race for money by millionaire
Democrat Jon Corzine, who has spent more than $6 million just to
air TV commercials over the past four weeks.
</P>
