<HEADLINE> Clinton Extends Liberians' Stay  </HEADLINE>
By ADAM GORLICK
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton on Thursday granted about
15,000 Liberians a last-minute extension to stay in America, but
their long-term future remains uncertain until Congress acts on a
measure to make them permanent residents.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton extended the Liberians' stay for one year, just hours
before a midnight deadline that would send them back.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton said he was worried that deportations could spur
countries in West Africa to also expel the thousands of Liberians
who fled there because of civil war. Forcing them to return would
''severely burden Liberia and cause instability in Liberia and in
the region,'' Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's a time for relief, not celebration,'' said Sen. Jack
Reed, D-R.I. ''We still confront the issue of letting them become
permanent members of our communities.''
</P>
<P>
   Reed is pushing for a bill that would grant the Liberians
permanent residency. Without it, they must apply for annual work
permits. Many Liberians have said it's difficult to land a
well-paying job because employers don't want to hire people who may
run the risk of being deported.
</P>
<P>
   ''Each time we make an extension, we add to the logic of letting
them become residents,'' Reed said. ''It's time we made it
permanent.''
</P>
<P>
   When the Liberians fled civil war in their country for the
United States in 1991, the government allowed them to stay for 12
months.
</P>
<P>
   They received extensions as the civil war continued. The
fighting ended in 1997 and U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno decided
last year that another extension would not be made. But the
administration concluded the Liberians would be in danger if they
returned home, and Clinton allowed them to stay in the United
States until Sept. 28, requiring the latest extension.
</P>
<P>
   About 4,000 Liberians live in Rhode Island. Many others settled
in Massachusetts and Illinois.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-28-00 1921 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
