AL-leading 45th homer as the Anaheim Angels beat Oakland 6-3 today, hurting the
Athletics' chances of making the AL playoffs. Oakland (88-70) lost for just the
second time in nine games and dropped one game behind Seattle (89-69) in the AL
West. The A's lead in the wild card race shrank to one game over Cleveland
(87-71).
AP NewsBrief By MARIA CODER 
