<HEADLINE> Auction of fiberglass cows nets over $1.3 million   </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - An auction of some of the bovine beauties that
were stationed around the city this summer has netted more than
$1.3 million for a variety of charities.
</P>
<P>
   Seventy-five of the fiberglass cow statues were auctioned on
Thursday night, with a total sale of $1,354,000, said a spokesman
for CowParade New York 2000. The highest seller was Tiffany Cow, a
statue of a sitting cow done in the style of a Tiffany
