<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woman stranded on side of mountain  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CORNWALL, N.Y. (AP) - A helicopter was sent from Albany Thursday
night to rescue a woman reported stranded on a ledge of Storm King
Mountain.
</P>
<P>
   The woman was apparently walking with a male acquaintance just
before 8 p.m. when they became separated. Her acquaintance
apparently was the one who called for help.
</P>
<P>
   Town of Cornwall police said they were unable to reach the woman
and were unsure whether the woman was hurt. They said she was not
adequately dressed for the anticipated 30 to 35 degree overnight
temperatures.
</P>
<P>
   Storm King Mountain is in Orange County and overlooks the Hudson
River.
</P>
</TEXT>
