<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-28 23:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> How College Football's Top 25 Fared  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   How the top 25 teams in The Associated Press' college
football
poll fared Thursday:
<TEXT>
<P>
   No. 1 Nebraska (3-0) did not play. Next: vs. Missouri, Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   No. 2 Florida State (5-0) beat Maryland 59-7, Thursday. Next: at
No. 10 Miami, Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   No. 3 Florida (4-0) did not play. Next: at Mississippi State,
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   No. 4 Virginia Tech (3-0) did not play. Next: at Boston College,
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   No. 5 Kansas State (4-0) did not play. Next: at Colorado,
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   No. 6 Washington (3-0) did not play. Next: at No. 20 Oregon,
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
