<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-28 23:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Avalanche 6, Stars 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS (AP) -- David Aebischer stopped Joe Nieuwendyk on a
penalty shot, and Adam Deadmarsh scored two power-play goals in
Colorado's 6-2 exhibition victory over Dallas on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   David Aebischer, who made 31 saves, stopped Nieuwendyk's attempt
with 1:45 left.
</P>
<P>
   Peter Forsberg also had a power-play goal, Chris Drury had a
goal and three assists, and John Klemm and Stephane Yelle added
goals for the Avalanche (4-2-1).
</P>
<P>
   Deadmarsh broke a 2-2 tie at 7:07 of the second period, and
Forsberg made it 4-2 with 3:12 left in the period.
</P>
<P>
   Jere Lehtinen scored twice for the Stars (3-2-3).
</P>
</TEXT>
