<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-28 23:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heat Sign Brunson, Robinson  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Rick Brunson, the free-agent point guard who spent
the last two seasons with the New York Knicks, signed with the
Miami Heat on Thursday. Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Brunson averaged 1.9 points and 1.3 assists in 37 games last
season while playing behind Charlie Ward and Chris Childs.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-4 guard, entering his fourth season, has career
averages of 2.7 points and 1.8 assists.
</P>
<P>
   The Heat also signed swingman Jamal Robinson.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-7 former Virginia player spent last season playing in
Lebanon and the United States Basketball League.
</P>
</TEXT>
